A magreza de Brad Pitt foi motivo de preocupação dos fãs, mas o ator fez questão de os tranquilizar e de garantir que está tudo bem. Depois da primeira entrevista à GQ após a separação com Angelina Jolie, o Pitt voltar a dar uma entrevista, desta vez à Associated Press.
O ator diz que compreende que as pessoas se preocupem com o seu bem-estar, mas garante que de momento está focado nos filhos. "Não sou suicida, nem nada do género. Ainda há muita beleza no mundo e muito amor. Muito amor para ser dado. Está tudo bem, isto é apenas a vida", disse Brad Pitt. "Os filhos são tudo, são a minha vida. O meu foco está neles, como sempre", afirmou.

Na última entrevista que deu, o artista admitiu que o álcool esteve no centro da separação e que teve de parar imediatamente.

Angelina e Brad Pitt estão separados desde 20 de setembro de 2016.

May 13, 2017 🎓
July 25th, 2010. Till the day I die I'll always remember this date. It's the day that I left my family, my friends, my life that I built growing up, and my country to come to the States to get a better education and a better future. 7 years later here I am a graduate with 3 degrees in engineering (Associate, Bachelor, and Masters). 7 years of hard work, good and bad days, meeting new people and making friends, and more. But now I move to better things bigger things and conquering life after college. To my family, THANK YOU SO MUCH for believing in me and supporting me all these years I know it was hard but you all were there for me. Dad oh Dad no matter what I say nothing will be enough for the things you've done for me to be where I am now, so thank you Baba habibi for the sacrifices that you've made and I know you'll make more for me. The strength that you had to send your son to the other half of the world away from you just so he can get a better life and education is unbelievable. Again from the bottom of my heart thank you!!! To my friends, oh god where do I begin. I've met a lot and I mean a lot of people the last couple of years but only few that I'm honored to call my friends. I don't wanna say names cause I know for sure I'm ganna forget some of ya. But every one of you knows what they mean to me. I wanna thank every single one of you for the best college years anyone can ask for, MAD LOVE TO YOU ALL!!
I know after this we all going our way doing our thing in different cities but I promise you that I'll keep in touch with you all as much as I can. Life is just getting started guys so let's go out there and show'em what us the Salukis are made of!!
And remember, ONCE A SALUKI ALWAYS A SALUKI!! GO DAWGS!! 🐾

Did you know that ZCenter has an Associate Board? The ZCenter Associate Board is a group of young professionals who raise funds and awareness to contribute to ZCenter's mission to end sexual violence!

ZCenter's Associate Board is an amazing way for passionate young professionals to give back, get involved, and invest in professional development! Keep an eye out for several upcoming Associate Board events or learn more and get involved, contact Victoria at vcelano@zcenter.org!
